Fix downloading videos by their name.

Arte changed its programs pages so that they do not include the arte plus 7
video frame. Therefore, using it to find the last video is not working anymore.

The default plus7 page: http://www.arte.tv/guide/fr/plus7/ provides a video
carrousel. It is using 'guide/fr/plus7.json' page to get the videos
informations.

Adapt the code to use this page as url source.
The videos names may appear multiple times if they are multiple videos
available. Use the first in the json by default, which should be the last one.

Fix: Downloading videos by their name do not work anymore #3

Refactoring to adapt to new ArtePlus7 interface.

Separate in two classes:
* Plus7Program to describe a page with a video.
* ArtePlus7 to help using the website API.

The whole videos json has been removed and should now be parsed from a
'text/javascript' tag in search results page.

Broke previous interface but keep cli working.

Add option to choose number of videos to download

 -n NUM_PROGRAMS
 --num-programs NUM_PROGRAMS

By default only download the last one, may try to download more if specified.

Add search option

 -s SEARCH
 --search SEARCH

In addition to '--program' to search for specific preconfigured programs,
allow searching for any text. The text will be passed directly as a
query_string to the search page.

Add a 'verbose' option

 -v
 --verbose
